research/history/memory.json.bak_corrupt_round141:1382:      "design_hypothesis": "After three distinct K32 soft-codebook backbones failed to beat the bucketed point under `EF=16`, the next severe-stagnation step should continue architecture search only along an already-registered but mechanistically different branch rather than return to scalar tweaks. `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual` is the strongest remaining soft-codebook variant by prior results and may yield a better small-K tradeoff at `K=32, EF=16` by using learned gating instead of bucket partitioning or hard routing.",
