research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/results.tsv:158:r156_1774273334	1774273334	ok	discard	0.09860044717788696	24	lowrank_gated_residual	16				/root/sparsify-ascend/checkpoints/research_agent/round_0156/round0156_standard_1774272974_dp2_bs1_ga8_ef16_k24_20260323_213621	2c0d5845052ac4f347378575b513bb00788175da			Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed. This follows the stagnation policy to stop minor tweaks, continues exploring materially different existing families, and targets a valuable smaller-K slot where a non-dominated tradeoff would still improve the frontier even if absolute FVU remains above the incumbent `K=32` point.	This is a clean single-variable architecture probe using an existing registered family. The main risk is that plain gating may repeat its weak `K=32` result, but `K=24` remains an uncovered tradeoff point and this family is still structurally distinct enough to justify one direct test there before concluding that learned gating is noncompetitive across the current EF=16 small-K lane. It is a more policy-consistent next action than returning to optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after both already failed recently.	/root/sparsify-ascend/research/history/logs/round0156_standard_1774272974.log
