research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0007.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the controlled same-family sweep with a parameter-only run at `K=1`, while pinning the established recipe (`ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). The `K=2` run remained keep-worthy, so the most informative next step is to finish the low-K trace before switching to routed variants or other families.",
