research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0001.json:83:    "description": "Added and registered `lowrank_two_stage_residual` in `sparsify/config.py` and `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`. The new class keeps the stable low-rank trunk, splits total K across two sparse residual passes, and reuses a shared decoder for both stages. Exact integration smoke test passed for `ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `K=32`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12` with forward+backward on CUDA. Recommended next run is a controlled full experiment at the established low-K recipe settings.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0108.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After nine non-improving rounds, the next useful move is a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than another low-rank/codebook variant; `adaptive_budget_topk` may improve the K=24 tradeoff by reallocating support across examples while keeping the same average sparsity target.","summary":"Severe stagnation is still active, so this round should not spend effort on more soft-codebook or scalar recipe tweaks. Run one architecture-comparison experiment at the valuable smaller-K anchor `K=24` with `adaptive_budget_topk`, holding the rest of the strong EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe fixed. This tests a qualitatively different dynamic-budget selector that has not been explored in the current search history and is directly aligned with the policy guidance to try a fundamentally different architecture.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"adaptive_budget_topk","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This obeys the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than tuning within a losing family, and it keeps K within the allowed operator set. The main risk is that the simpler non-low-rank baseline may underperform on absolute FVU, but the mechanism is different enough to justify one clean probe at the K=24 frontier slot.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"adaptive_budget_topk"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_residual_vq` also lost at `K=24`, severe stagnation remained active and the search should continue with a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism rather than more low-rank or codebook variations.","Round 108 should probe `adaptive_budget_topk` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe to test whether dynamic budget allocation helps the mid-K Pareto lane.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone."],"next_hypotheses":["If `adaptive_budget_topk` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the dynamic-budget benefit persists in the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another fundamentally different non-codebook mechanism rather than returning to soft-codebook cleanup.","If it runs but is noisy and close, do one confirmatory repeat at the same `K=24` anchor before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0103.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The `LR=1.6e-3` exploitation probe at `K=96` clearly underperformed, so `3.2e-3` should remain the routed-family baseline and the next clean exploitation dimension is auxiliary dead-feature pressure. The specific hypothesis is that a small nonzero `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` can improve feature utilization for `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at the valuable `K=96` anchor without the severe optimization regression seen from lowering LR.","summary":"Run one parameter-only exploitation experiment at `K=96` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `LR=3.2e-3` fixed while changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.0` to `0.01`. Success criterion: beat the current `K=96` frontier anchor FVU (`0.06254687905311584`) and determine whether light aux-k pressure improves the routed family on the strongest smaller-K high-quality tradeoff point.","change_type":"param_only","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This follows the exploitation policy and changes exactly one parameter after the lower-LR test failed badly. I kept the target at `K=96` because it remains the more valuable Pareto anchor than `K=128` if quality improves. The main risk is that aux pressure may disturb the routed recipe the same way it hurt the plain soft-codebook family, but this is the cleanest remaining exploitation branch.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.01"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 102 showed `LR=1.6e-3` is a clear regression for `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=96`, so `LR=3.2e-3` should remain the routed-family baseline.","Round 103 should switch exploitation dimensions from learning rate to aux-k pressure while keeping the valuable `K=96` routed anchor fixed.","Keep all recipe fields fixed except `AUXK_ALPHA`; this isolates whether light dead-feature pressure improves the current best routed family without confounding with another LR change."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` wins at `K=96`, propagate the same aux setting to `K=128` under the fixed routed recipe to test whether the gain generalizes to the top-quality anchor.","If it is close but still behind at `K=96`, test the stronger `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` before abandoning aux tuning on the routed family.","If it clearly loses at `K=96`, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` as the routed baseline and use the next exploitation round for the remaining routed LR values only if policy still requires exhausting them."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0004.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed and dropping only `K` from 16 to 8 will test whether this family can add a further non-dominated low-support point on the Pareto frontier, accepting some FVU increase if the tradeoff remains competitive.","summary":"Continue the same-family low-K sweep with a parameter-only run at `K=8`, while pinning the existing low-K recipe (`ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). The `K=16` result was good enough to justify tracing the tail lower before switching families or introducing routing changes.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This follows the current frontier logic cleanly: one variable changes, the recipe stays controlled, and the next most informative question is whether the same family still holds up at substantially smaller support.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 4 extends the controlled K sweep for `lowrank_two_stage_residual` from 16 to 8 with all other recipe fields pinned.","The current low-K lane is yielding monotonic frontier points at K=32, 24, and 16, so the most informative next step is to test whether the same family remains Pareto-relevant at K=8 before trying a new architecture."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` stays competitive, continue to `K=4` on the same family to finish mapping the low-K tail.","If `K=8` degrades sharply, hold `K` near 16-24 and test a routed variant to improve support allocation.","If `K=8` is borderline but promising, keep the family fixed and adjust stage allocation rather than changing the broader recipe."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0116.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At K=24, the plain two-stage soft-codebook model is close to optimal but may still be missing the benefit of explicit support routing once the sparse budget is front-loaded. A new `routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` family could beat the K=24 anchor by combining the near-miss asymmetric budget split with router-guided support selection from the current high-K winner.","summary":"Severe stagnation has reached 17 rounds, so this round should introduce another genuinely new architecture rather than another scalar tweak or a repeat of a recent losing family. The most defensible next move is a code edit on the strongest current backbone: add `routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` under `sparsify/` and test it at the frontier-relevant K=24 slot with the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This is a new family, not a parameter tweak, and it stays tightly coupled to the strongest observed mechanisms instead of branching into a disconnected idea after many losses. The main risk is that routing and asymmetry may not be complementary at K=24, but the asymmetric non-routed variant was already close enough that this combination is a reasonable severe-stagnation probe.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 116 should satisfy severe-stagnation policy with a genuinely new architecture family rather than another parameter-only retry.","Implement `routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as a routed variant of the asymmetric two-stage soft-codebook family so the main new hypothesis is whether explicit router-guided support helps once stage budget is front-loaded at K=24.","Complete the full integration chain before training: config whitelist, `_get_sae_class()` dispatch, concrete class in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`, then exact instantiate/forward/backward smoke test at `(architecture=routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=24, EF=12)`.","Keep the launch contract minimal and exact so the result remains attributable to architecture alone at K=24."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at K=24, follow with K=16 to test whether the same combination helps more in the smaller-K lane.","If it clearly loses at K=24, continue severe-stagnation search with another genuinely different new family rather than further soft-codebook stage-splitting variants.","If the smoke test passes but full training fails, repair the new architecture-specific blocker without changing the family or env overrides."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0043.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After repeated failures from low-rank variants and gated branch variants, a fundamentally different sparsity mechanism may help the mid-K frontier: `jumprelu` at `K=24, EF=12` could improve support quality versus plain top-k selection and beat the current `K=24` point without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a strict architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=12` using `jumprelu` with the settled recipe (`OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). This matches the severe-stagnation policy by trying a different architecture family rather than another scalar sweep, while targeting a frontier-relevant smaller-K tradeoff point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"jumprelu","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, and K sweeps because 8 non-improving rounds means minor tweaks are exhausted. I also avoided another low-rank or gating variant after three clear architecture losses in that neighborhood, and kept all non-architecture fields fixed for a clean comparison.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"jumprelu"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 43 continues severe-stagnation recovery with another fundamentally different built-in architecture rather than returning to scalar tuning.","Use a clean architecture-only test at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields pinned explicitly.","`jumprelu` tests a different sparsity mechanism than the recent low-rank, grouped, whitened, and branch-mixing families."],"next_hypotheses":["If `jumprelu` is close but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to check whether thresholded sparsity helps more under tighter budgets.","If `jumprelu` clearly loses at K=24, reject this family quickly and move to another non-lowrank architecture such as `two_stage_residual` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `jumprelu` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain generalizes across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
