research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0104.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After five non-improving rounds, minor recipe tweaks on the current routed and plain winners are no longer the highest-value move. A fundamentally different architecture is warranted, and the best next test is `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` at the smaller frontier-relevant `K=24` anchor: grouping may regularize support allocation in the mid-K regime without the instability that caused routed collapse at `K=32`, potentially creating a new non-dominated point below the current plain two-stage soft-codebook `K=24` frontier.","summary":"Run one architecture-comparison experiment at `K=24` with `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. Success criterion: beat the current `K=24` frontier anchor FVU (`0.09216673672199249`) and determine whether grouped soft-codebook support is a better mid-K backbone than continued tuning of routed/plain two-stage variants.","change_type":"param_only","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"incubating","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by switching to a genuinely different built-in architecture instead of another scalar tweak. I chose `K=24` because smaller-K improvements are more valuable than chasing the already-strong high-K anchors, and this slot is still owned by the plain family with room for a different architecture to win. The main risk is that grouping helps only at low K and will not outperform the plain two-stage soft-codebook recipe in the mid-K band.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Severe stagnation policy triggered after five non-improving rounds, so round 104 should stop scalar exploitation and switch to a fundamentally different architecture.","Choose `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` as the next architecture because it already showed some promise at low K and offers a qualitatively different support-allocation mechanism without introducing new code.","Target `K=24` first because improving a smaller-K frontier slot is more valuable than additional high-K probing, and the routed family has already shown instability when pushed downward."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=24`, run the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to map whether grouping is broadly useful in the mid-K regime.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=24`, consider one confirmatory run at `K=32` before discarding the grouped soft-codebook family.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, reject this grouped branch for mid-K and move the next severe-stagnation round to a different existing soft-codebook family such as `lowrank_gated_soft_codebook_residual`."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0134.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Adam may be failing specifically in the brittle low-K bucketed regime rather than across the whole `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` family. Testing the same EF=16 recipe at `K=64` isolates optimizer sensitivity on a stronger mid-K frontier point and could improve FVU without sacrificing a non-dominated tradeoff.","summary":"Run a parameter-only optimizer probe on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=64, EF=16`, switching from `signum` to `adam` while keeping the rest of the recipe fixed. This checks whether the recent Adam failure was K32-specific and gives a cleaner read on whether Adam is worth keeping alive on the current leading family.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This stays within the operator-requested runtime axes and avoids unsupported loss-function plumbing through the fixed launcher. It is not the highest-value smaller-K target, but after Adam and Hadamard both failed at K32, a K64 control is the cleanest way to determine whether Adam is broadly bad under EF=16 or only bad in the tightest bucketed regime.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 134 should use `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=64` as the optimizer control after Adam failed badly at K32 under the same EF=16 family.","Keep the override set minimal and explicit so attribution stays on optimizer rather than architecture, EF, or aux drift.","If Adam is still poor at K64, treat `adam` as broadly unpromising for the current EF=16 bucketed backbone and stop spending rounds on it without a stronger reason."],"next_hypotheses":["If Adam improves the K64 bucketed point, propagate Adam to K96 or K128 to see whether the gain is a general mid/high-K effect before revisiting K32 with a retuned LR.","If Adam is neutral or worse at K64, deprioritize optimizer swaps on the bucketed family and return to supported preprocessing probes on a different existing backbone.","If Adam is close but noisy at K64, run one confirmatory repeat on the same target rather than branching to another architecture."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0074.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` has already established non-dominated wins at `K=24` and `K=32` under the fixed `EF=12` / `signum` / `LR=3.2e-3` recipe, so the highest-value single-variable follow-up is a controlled `K=16` run to test whether the same family can replace the current `K=16` anchor and extend the frontier downward in K.","summary":"Run one parameter-only experiment at `K=16` with the existing `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` recipe. This is the cleanest next comparison after rounds 72-73: same architecture family, same optimizer and LR, only `K` changes. Success means beating the current `K=16` frontier point (`0.10692943632602692` from `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`) and showing the hybrid spans `K=16/24/32`, not just isolated wins at `K=24` and `K=32`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"promote_to_mainline","self_review":"This keeps to one hypothesis and one primary variable. I avoided a new family because the current hybrid is already showing a credible mid-K lane; testing `K=16` is more informative for the Pareto frontier than another recipe tweak. No code change is needed because the family is already registered and previously trained successfully.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 74 should be a controlled parameter-only probe of `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16` after clear wins at `K=24` and `K=32` under the fixed `EF=12` / `signum` / `LR=3.2e-3` / `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` recipe.","Success criterion is beating the current `K=16` frontier anchor (`lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, FVU `0.10692943632602692`) to show the hybrid spans more of the mid/low-K Pareto frontier, not just `K=24` and `K=32`."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16` wins, test `K=8` to see whether the hybrid can push even further down the frontier.","If `K=16` is close but slightly behind, run one confirmatory rerun before concluding the hybrid's advantage starts at `K=24`.","If `K=16` clearly loses, keep `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as the best `K=1/24/32` specialist and retain `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`."],"primary_variable":"k"}
