research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0144.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After three non-improving rounds on pure K descent, the bucketed backbone likely needs recipe exploitation rather than further sparsity pressure. A stronger auxiliary feature-usage penalty may help the low-K regime use its limited capacity more efficiently, so testing `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` at the best current small-K bucketed point (`K=16`) is the cleanest one-variable probe.","summary":"Run a pure auxiliary-loss sweep on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`, keeping architecture, optimizer, LR, preprocessing, and `EF=16` fixed while changing only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.0` to `0.0625`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the explicit exploitation guidance, avoids new architectures, and changes exactly one parameter. I chose the `K=16` bucketed point instead of high-K anchors because it is the current practical lower bound for this family after `K=8` failed, so improving it is more valuable for the Pareto frontier than further polishing `K=128`.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0625"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 144 switches from K-axis exploration to exploitation after three non-improving rounds and tests whether stronger auxiliary usage pressure can improve the current low-K bucketed recipe.","This round isolates `AUXK_ALPHA` on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`, which is the most valuable current small-K anchor after `K=8` regressed too far."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` improves `K=16`, propagate the same aux setting to `K=24` or `K=32` to check whether the gain is a real family-level recipe improvement.","If it underperforms but training looks smooth, try the exploitation LR sweep next at `K=16` with `LR=4e-4` before concluding the current bucketed recipe is saturated.","If it destabilizes or clearly worsens convergence, keep `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` as the bucketed baseline and move to an LR-only probe on the same `K=16` anchor."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
