research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0158.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The Adam probes on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` show a classic LR-mismatch pattern rather than a dead optimizer: `LR=3.2e-3` at `K=32` collapsed to `FVU=0.1557`, while `LR=8e-4` recovered to `0.0895` but still drifted upward late versus the stable signum run. A further drop to `LR=4e-4` on the same `K=32, EF=16` anchor is the cleanest single-variable test for whether Adam can stabilize and beat the current signum point.","summary":"Retune Adam downward again on the strongest current small-K backbone by holding architecture, `K=32`, `EF=16`, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed, and changing only the optimizer recipe to `adam` at `LR=4e-4`. This follows the operator guidance not to discard an optimizer after one mismatched retune and uses the existing curve evidence that Adam is improving as LR falls.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a single-hypothesis optimizer follow-up grounded in observed training behavior, not another architecture churn round. The main risk is that Adam remains intrinsically weaker on this backbone, but the prior `3.2e-3 -> 8e-4` improvement is strong enough that one more downward retune is justified before abandoning the optimizer axis.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 158 stops the unsuccessful architecture churn and resumes the operator-prioritized optimizer search on the strongest current EF=16 backbone.","Rationale: on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=32`, Adam improved sharply from `FVU=0.1557` at `LR=3.2e-3` to `0.0895` at `LR=8e-4`, but the late-training curve still looked unstable versus signum, so the next informative probe is `LR=4e-4` rather than discarding Adam."],"next_hypotheses":["If Adam `4e-4` wins cleanly at `K=32`, propagate the same optimizer recipe to `K=64` to test whether the gain extends to another valuable smaller-K frontier point.","If Adam `4e-4` is still unstable or shows late drift, lower to `2e-4` on the same `K=32` anchor before concluding the optimizer is noncompetitive.","If Adam `4e-4` is smooth but clearly weaker than signum, treat optimizer choice as secondary for this backbone and shift to another under-explored non-architecture axis."],"primary_variable":"optimizer"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0095.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The routed soft-codebook two-stage family has now produced frontier improvements through `K=32`, so the next clean map point is `K=64` to test whether the same architectural gain persists beyond the current low/mid-K band and creates a stronger high-K anchor.","summary":"Run one parameter-only follow-up at `K=64` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EF=12`, `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed. This extends the same successful recipe to the next allowed K anchor and checks whether routing remains beneficial as sparse budget increases.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is the highest-signal next step because the family has already improved adjacent anchors up to `K=32`, and changing only `K` preserves a clean attribution. The main risk is that routing benefits saturate by `K=32`, but testing `K=64` is the right way to determine whether the family should become the default backbone beyond the current frontier band.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"64"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["r95 should extend `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to `K=64` after frontier improvements at `K=16`, `K=24`, and `K=32`.","Keep the recipe fixed and change only `K`; this isolates whether the routed soft-codebook advantage persists into the higher-K regime.","A `K=64` win would suggest the routed soft-codebook family is not just a low-K improvement but a broader EF=12 backbone candidate."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` wins at `K=64`, test it at `K=96` or `K=128` under the same recipe to map the upper end of the family.","If it is close but slightly behind at `K=64`, try one targeted routing-temperature adjustment before giving up on the family at higher K.","If it clearly loses at `K=64`, conclude that routing helps primarily up to the `K=32` regime and pivot to a different architecture family for higher-K anchors."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0111.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After twelve non-improving rounds, another fundamentally different selector is warranted; `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff than recent gated, adaptive-budget, and discrete branches by smoothing support selection on top of the proven low-rank residual trunk.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the recent K=24 probes across gated, adaptive-budget, and VQ-style branches all underperformed the current frontier. The next clean architecture comparison should stay on the valuable `K=24` anchor but switch to `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`, which offers a distinct sparse-selection mechanism from the families tried in rounds 107 to 110 while preserving the strong low-rank residual backbone. Keep the rest of the winning mid-K recipe fixed so the result isolates architecture alone.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than making another minor tweak, keeps K within the allowed operator set, and targets a meaningful smaller-K frontier slot. The risk is that prior older-budget evidence for this family was only modest, but it is still a more defensible next probe than revisiting recently failing mechanisms.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_gated_residual` also lost at `K=24`, recent selector-focused branches remain uncompetitive against the current mid-K frontier.","Round 111 should test `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as another fundamentally different sparse-selection mechanism on the low-rank backbone.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture rather than recipe drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to adaptive-budget or codebook variants.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0044.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The recent failures suggest the extra low-rank/gating structure may be hurting rather than helping, so a simpler coarse-to-fine residual stack may recover mid-K quality: `two_stage_residual` at `K=24, EF=12` could outperform the recent non-lowrank misses and potentially challenge the current `K=24` frontier point without increasing K or EF.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=24, EF=12` with `two_stage_residual` under the pinned recipe `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. This follows the severe-stagnation policy by trying another fundamentally different built-in architecture and avoids any further minor scalar sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"two_stage_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"I avoided LR, aux, and expansion-factor tweaks because nine no-improve rounds means scalar tuning is exhausted. I also moved away from low-rank, whitening, and gating after repeated clear losses, while keeping K fixed at a frontier-relevant value for a clean architecture-only read.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 44 continues severe-stagnation recovery with a simpler non-lowrank residual architecture after `multi_branch_gated` and `jumprelu` both failed badly at K=24.","Keep the test architecture-only at K=24, EF=12 with all recipe fields explicitly pinned.","`two_stage_residual` checks whether hierarchical residual coding helps mid-K without the added complexity of low-rank trunks or learned gating."],"next_hypotheses":["If `two_stage_residual` is competitive but slightly worse at K=24, test K=16 to see whether staged residual coding helps more under tighter budgets.","If `two_stage_residual` clearly loses at K=24, reject this branch and move to another fundamentally different family such as `batch_topk` or `residual_vq` rather than any scalar sweep.","If `two_stage_residual` wins at K=24, follow with K=16 or K=32 to map whether the gain is localized or extends across the mid-K band."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
