research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0001.json:17:    "hypothesis": "With an empty EF=12 frontier, the highest-value Round 1 move is to establish a clean `topk` anchor at the policy reference recipe before any LR or optimizer sweep. A full baseline run at `ARCHITECTURE=topk K=128 EXPANSION_FACTOR=12 OPTIMIZER=signum LR=8e-4` will give the first trustworthy curve shape for this regime and prevent later tuning rounds from being confounded by an unverified starting point.",
