research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0127.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The bucketed locality bias that improved both K=16 and K=32 may also create a better mid-low-K tradeoff at K=24 under EF=16 by preserving the same structured competition pattern in the gap between those two new wins.","summary":"The bucketed family has now produced real frontier gains at both K=16 and K=32, so the highest-value next step is to interpolate the missing K=24 slot rather than jumping to a larger K. This keeps architecture and recipe fixed, changes only K, and directly tests whether the new family owns a broader contiguous low-K region instead of just two isolated points.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the cleanest frontier-mapping follow-up after back-to-back improvements: probe the missing interior K value with the same recipe. The main risk is that the bucketed advantage is non-monotonic across K, but K=24 is exactly the right place to resolve that uncertainty while prioritizing smaller K.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 127 maps the interior K=24 point after the bucketed family improved the frontier at both K=16 and K=32 under EF=16.","Hold architecture and recipe fixed so the result isolates the K-axis and determines whether bucketed locality yields a contiguous low-K frontier segment.","K=24 is higher value than pushing to larger K because smaller-K non-dominated tradeoffs remain the main objective."],"next_hypotheses":["If K=24 is competitive, continue mapping the bucketed family at K=64 to test how far the benefit extends into the higher-K lane.","If K=24 underperforms while K=16 and K=32 stay strong, treat the bucketed family as having a non-monotonic sweet spot and confirm with a repeat only if the miss is small.","If K=24 improves clearly, consider promoting the bucketed family as the default EF=16 backbone for the low-to-mid-K regime."],"primary_variable":"k"}
