research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0112.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After thirteen non-improving rounds, the next useful step is another fundamentally different architecture rather than any recipe tweak; `bucketed_lowrank_residual` may recover a better K=24 tradeoff by routing samples between specialized low-rank residual dictionaries instead of forcing one global selector.","summary":"Severe stagnation remains active, and the recent K=24 probes across adaptive-budget, gated, and JumpReLU support-selection variants all failed to beat the current frontier. The next clean architecture comparison should stay on the valuable `K=24` anchor but switch to `bucketed_lowrank_residual`, which offers a distinct conditional-dictionary mechanism from the families tried in rounds 109 to 111 while keeping the rest of the strong EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe fixed. This isolates architecture alone and tests whether sample-conditioned dictionary choice is more effective than changing only the selector.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"small_k_frontier","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by changing architecture rather than making another minor tweak, keeps K within the allowed operator set, and targets a meaningful smaller-K frontier slot. The main risk is that prior older-budget evidence for this family was not strong, but it remains a more distinct and defensible next probe than revisiting recently failing selector variants.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["After `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` also lost at `K=24`, recent selector-focused low-rank branches remain uncompetitive against the current mid-K frontier.","Round 112 should test `bucketed_lowrank_residual` at `K=24` under the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3 recipe as a more structurally different conditional-dictionary mechanism.","Keep the override set minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture rather than recipe drift."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with the same fixed recipe at `K=32` to see whether the conditional-dictionary benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, continue severe-stagnation search with another distinct existing family rather than returning to recent selector variants.","If it is close but noisy at `K=24`, run one confirmatory repeat before promoting or discarding the family."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0155.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After plain soft-codebook, grouped soft-codebook, and residual-VQ all failed at `K=24`, the next severe-stagnation move should remain a fundamentally different existing architecture rather than any minor recipe tweak. `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is the strongest remaining candidate for this slot because it changes the sparsity mechanism itself from top-k/codebook-style selection to thresholded JumpReLU gating, which may preserve a better low-K tradeoff under the fixed `EF=16` signum recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed. This follows the stagnation policy to stop minor tweaks, continues exploring materially different existing families, and targets a valuable smaller-K slot where a non-dominated result would still improve the frontier even without beating the incumbent `K=32` point on absolute FVU.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean single-variable architecture probe using an existing registered family. The main risk is that JumpReLU may again underperform the bucketed backbone as it did at `K=32`, but `K=24` is a different tradeoff point and still worth probing before concluding that this sparsity mechanism is noncompetitive across the current EF=16 low-K lane. It is a more defensible next action than returning to optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after those avenues already failed recently.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_jumprelu_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 155 continues severe-stagnation recovery with another fundamentally different existing architecture at `K=24, EF=16`: `lowrank_jumprelu_residual`.","This round isolates the sparsity mechanism change only, keeping the recipe pinned to signum + `LR=3.2e-3` + no Hadamard so attribution stays on architecture.","If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` also loses clearly at `K=24`, treat JumpReLU-style selection as noncompetitive in the current small-K EF=16 lane and continue to the next distinct existing family rather than returning to minor tweaks."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_jumprelu_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to map whether thresholded gating improves the low-K tradeoff curve further down the frontier.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=24` as another structurally different selection mechanism rather than returning to scalar tuning.","If it clearly loses at `K=24`, deprioritize JumpReLU in the current EF=16 regime and move to the next fundamentally different existing architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0102.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After three non-improving rounds, the highest-value exploitation move is to keep the current best family fixed on the more valuable high-quality smaller-K anchor `K=96` and sweep learning rate. The specific hypothesis is that lowering `LR` from `3.2e-3` to `1.6e-3` for `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` may improve optimization stability enough to beat the current `K=96` frontier point without giving up the stronger Pareto tradeoff relative to `K=128`.","summary":"Run one parameter-only exploitation experiment at `K=96` with `routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, keeping `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` fixed while changing only `LR` from `3.2e-3` to `1.6e-3`. Success criterion: beat the current `K=96` frontier anchor FVU (`0.06254687905311584`) and determine whether the routed family benefits from a lower LR at the most valuable high-quality smaller-K slot.","change_type":"param_only","expected_win":"frontier_improve","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This follows the explicit stagnation guidance to switch into exploitation on the current best family and changes exactly one parameter. I chose `K=96` instead of `K=128` because the smaller-K high-quality point is the stronger Pareto target if quality can be maintained or improved. The main risk is that `3.2e-3` was already near-optimal for this family and lowering LR will slow progress or underfit.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"96"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Stagnation policy triggered after three non-improving rounds, so round 102 should switch to exploitation on the current best routed family rather than continue plain-family cleanup.","Choose `K=96` as the exploitation anchor because it is a more valuable Pareto point than `K=128` if FVU improves under the same family.","Keep all recipe fields fixed except `LR`; this is the first routed-family LR sweep point and tests whether lower LR improves the high-quality smaller-K lane."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=1.6e-3` wins at `K=96`, propagate the same LR to `K=128` under the fixed routed recipe to see whether the improvement generalizes to the top-quality anchor.","If it is close but still behind at `K=96`, test the next lower routed-family LR (`4e-4`) before switching dimensions.","If it clearly loses at `K=96`, restore `LR=3.2e-3` as the routed baseline and move the next exploitation round to `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` at the same `K=96` anchor."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0108.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0145.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` worsened the `K=16` bucketed run, so the next exploitation step should test whether the current low-K bucketed recipe is learning-rate mismatched rather than fundamentally saturated. A lower `LR=4e-4` is the highest-priority single-variable probe because it is explicitly suggested by the latest result and may improve convergence stability at the current practical lower-bound anchor.","summary":"Run a pure learning-rate sweep on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` at `K=16`, keeping architecture, optimizer, aux loss, preprocessing, and `EF=16` fixed while changing only `LR` from `3.2e-3` to `4e-4`.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the exploitation policy after four non-improving rounds, avoids new architectures, and changes exactly one parameter. I chose the `K=16` anchor because it is the most valuable exposed small-K bucketed point after `K=8` failed, and improving it would matter more for the frontier than polishing already-strong high-K anchors.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"4e-4"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 145 continues exploitation on the bucketed backbone after the stronger aux-loss probe underperformed, shifting to an LR-only test at the most valuable low-K anchor.","This round isolates whether the `K=16` bucketed recipe is overshooting under `LR=3.2e-3`; `LR=4e-4` is the first lower-LR probe because it is closer to the current working regime than `2e-4` while still being a substantial stability test."],"next_hypotheses":["If `LR=4e-4` improves `K=16`, propagate that LR to `K=24` to test whether the gain generalizes across the low-K bucketed frontier.","If `LR=4e-4` underperforms but training is smooth, test the remaining lower LR `2e-4` before concluding that this backbone truly prefers the higher step size.","If `LR=4e-4` clearly slows convergence too much, restore `LR=3.2e-3` as the bucketed baseline and shift the next round to a preprocessing or optimizer probe rather than further low-LR descent."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0126.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"The bucketed locality bias that improved the K=16 point may also strengthen the low-to-mid-K lane at K=32 under EF=16 by reducing cross-bucket competition without the instability of full routing.","summary":"Round 125 produced a real frontier improvement at K=16 with `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual`, so the next disciplined step is to map whether that gain extends to the adjacent frontier-relevant K=32 slot. This keeps the architecture and recipe fixed while changing only K, which is the highest-value follow-up for determining whether the new family deserves promotion beyond a single-point win.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This is the correct post-win follow-up: hold architecture and recipe constant, move to the nearest valuable K slot, and test whether the improvement generalizes into the low-to-mid-K frontier. The main risk is that the bucketed inductive bias helps only at very small K, but that is exactly what this round will resolve.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 126 follows the new K=16 improvement by mapping the same bucketed family at K=32 under the fixed EF=16 regime.","Hold architecture and recipe fixed so attribution stays on the K-axis after the K=16 win.","A competitive K=32 result would indicate the bucketed family is not just a one-off small-K repair but a broader frontier candidate in the EF=16 regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If the bucketed family is competitive at K=32, test K=24 or K=64 next to map the extent of its frontier coverage under EF=16.","If K=32 is clearly worse while K=16 remains strong, treat the bucketed family as a specialized small-K architecture and probe K=24 rather than pushing higher.","If K=32 nearly matches the incumbent but is noisy, run one confirmatory repeat at K=32 before promoting the family further."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/15_20260326_190606/round_summaries/round_0003.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0149.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Eight non-improving rounds indicate the recent grouped, residual-VQ, and JumpReLU branches are not opening a new frontier, so the next step should remain a genuinely different existing architecture at the key `K=32, EF=16` slot. `lowrank_gated_residual` is the strongest remaining fundamentally different candidate because it uses learned gating without soft-codebook composition, and earlier results suggest it can be competitive in adjacent K regimes even though it has not yet been tested at this exact low-K EF=16 slot under the current pinned recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=32, EF=16` by switching to `lowrank_gated_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_gated_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation directive to stop minor tweaks and keep trying fundamentally different existing architectures. I kept `K=32` because it remains the most valuable exposed EF=16 frontier slot for a clean architecture comparison, and I pinned the rest of the recipe so the result isolates whether plain learned gating beats the exhausted soft-codebook-style families.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_gated_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 149 continues severe-stagnation recovery by testing `lowrank_gated_residual` at `K=32, EF=16` after grouped soft-codebook, residual-VQ, and JumpReLU comparisons all failed to threaten the current bucketed frontier point.","Rationale: plain lowrank gating is structurally different from the recently exhausted soft-codebook and quantized families, and it has shown credible performance in other K regimes, making it a sensible remaining architecture probe at the most valuable exposed slot."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_gated_residual` is competitive at `K=32`, follow with `K=24` to map whether gating creates a better small-K tradeoff curve than the bucketed backbone.","If it is close but still worse than bucketed, shift the next round to a non-architecture axis such as preprocessing or optimizer on the strongest current bucketed anchor.","If it clearly loses at `K=32`, treat plain lowrank gating as noncompetitive in the current EF=16 regime and move to the next underexplored axis rather than more architecture churn."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0040.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five rounds of stagnation mean scalar tweaks are exhausted, so the next move should be a fundamentally different architecture under a controlled recipe rather than more LR or aux changes. `lowrank_grouped_residual` is a materially different low-EF family that enforces group-local competition, and testing it at the frontier-relevant `K=16, EF=12` slot can reveal whether structured support selection improves the mid-K tradeoff over `lowrank_two_stage_residual`.","summary":"Run a pure architecture comparison at `K=16, EF=12` by switching from `lowrank_two_stage_residual` to `lowrank_grouped_residual` while keeping optimizer, learning rate, expansion factor, and aux fixed to the settled mid-K recipe. This satisfies severe-stagnation guidance by opening a genuinely different architecture branch instead of continuing minor scalar sweeps.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy directly: stop minor tweaks and try a fundamentally different architecture. `K=16` is the cleanest target because it is frontier-relevant, uses the strongest settled `EF=12` recipe, and gives a controlled readout on whether grouped competition helps in the transition band.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 40 exits the failed scalar-exploitation loop under severe stagnation and opens a materially different architecture branch instead of continuing LR or aux sweeps.","The new test is `lowrank_grouped_residual` at `K=16, EF=12` under the settled `signum`, `LR=3.2e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` recipe to evaluate whether group-local sparse competition improves the mid-K frontier band."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_residual` wins at `K=16`, continue the same architecture-only comparison at `K=24` before changing any scalar hyperparameters.","If it is close but slightly worse at `K=16`, keep the family active and test one adjacent K to see whether the benefit is band-specific.","If it clearly loses at `K=16`, reject this branch and move to another substantially different built-in architecture rather than returning to minor sweeps."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0131.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0143.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"`bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` stayed on a smooth enough degradation path when moving from `K=24` to `K=16` (`FVU 0.0889 -> 0.1015`), so the highest-value single-variable probe is to continue the same descent to `K=8`. Even with a further FVU increase, a credible `K=8, EF=16` point could extend the Pareto frontier toward materially lower online cost.","summary":"Run a pure K-axis experiment on the current strongest EF=16 backbone by holding recipe and preprocessing fixed and reducing only `K` from 16 to 8.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_k","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This respects the one-variable rule and keeps `EXPANSION_FACTOR=16` pinned. I am deferring the hinted optimizer/preprocessing probes by one round because round 142 produced a useful smaller-K archive point, so the cleanest next frontier-maintenance action is to finish mapping whether this backbone still has a viable `K=8` tradeoff.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"8"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 143 hypothesis: continue the pure K-axis descent on `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` by testing `K=8` with architecture, optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing unchanged.","Rationale: round 142 showed a moderate rather than catastrophic degradation at `K=16`, so `K=8` is now the highest-information remaining point on the allowed K grid for determining how far this backbone can extend the low-K frontier under the fixed EF=16 regime."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=8` forms a non-dominated point, continue the same K-axis descent to `K=4` to map the extreme low-K tail on this backbone.","If `K=8` regresses sharply, keep `K=16` as the practical lower bound for this recipe and shift the next round to a preprocessing probe such as `USE_HADAMARD=1` at fixed `K=24` or `K=16`.","If `K=8` is close but noisy, run one confirmatory repeat before concluding whether the bucketed backbone truly supports the sub-16 regime."],"primary_variable":"k"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0009.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Keeping `lowrank_two_stage_residual` fixed at `K=16` and reducing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` from 12 to 8 will test whether this family can add a lower-cost non-dominated point without giving up too much FVU.","summary":"Use a parameter-only probe on the existing `lowrank_two_stage_residual` family at `K=16`, changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR` to `8` while pinning `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, and `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`. The low-K tail has already been mapped from `K=32` down to `K=1`, so the next clean frontier question is whether the same family can trade some reconstruction quality for a meaningfully smaller model at a proven useful K.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"smaller_ef","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"stabilize","self_review":"This avoids the prior policy-rejected code-plus-architecture move, preserves strict variable isolation with `primary_variable=expansion_factor`, and probes the remaining frontier dimension on a stable family.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"8"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"1.6e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 9 shifts from the completed K sweep to an EF sweep on the same family, using `K=16` as the anchor and changing only `EXPANSION_FACTOR`.","The previous routed-family proposal was policy-rejected because it coupled code editing with an architecture change, so the next step should stay parameter-only and isolate a single frontier dimension."],"next_hypotheses":["If `K=16, EF=8` stays competitive, continue to `K=24, EF=8` or `K=8, EF=8` to map the lower-EF lane.","If `EF=8` degrades too much at `K=16`, keep `EF=12` for this family and revisit architecture changes only after a clean code-only integration plan.","If `EF=8` is borderline but promising, test `EF=10` at the same `K=16` to refine the cost-quality knee."],"primary_variable":"expansion_factor"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0146.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Five non-improving rounds indicate the current bucketed recipe is locally exhausted, so the next step should be a genuinely different encoder structure rather than another scalar tweak. `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is the best remaining structurally distinct, already-registered candidate for the `K=32, EF=16` slot because it showed plausible though weaker results at `K=24` and `K=16`, and grouping may allocate limited low-K capacity differently enough to beat the current non-bucketed alternatives under the fixed recipe.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=32, EF=16` by swapping from `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` to `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This follows the severe-stagnation policy by abandoning minor recipe tweaks and testing a fundamentally different existing architecture. I kept `K=32` because it is the highest-value exposed EF=16 frontier slot for architecture comparisons, and I kept the rest of the recipe pinned so the result isolates architectural effect.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 146 exits the failed bucketed scalar-tuning loop after five non-improving rounds and returns to a materially different architecture on the most valuable exposed EF=16 frontier slot.","`lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` is chosen because it is an existing registered family with credible but underexplored low-K priors, and grouping offers a different capacity-allocation mechanism than the recently exhausted bucketed/two-stage/routed/gated variants."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_grouped_soft_codebook_residual` improves the `K=32, EF=16` slot, continue within that family by probing `K=24` or `K=16` to map whether it creates a better small-K frontier.","If it is close but still worse than bucketed, switch the next round to an underexplored training axis such as preprocessing or optimizer on the strongest current bucketed anchor rather than more architecture churn.","If it clearly loses at `K=32`, treat grouped soft-codebook routing as noncompetitive under the current regime and move to a non-architecture axis next."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0056.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0115.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At K=24, the current two-stage soft-codebook backbone may be wasting scarce support by splitting K evenly across stages. A new `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` family that allocates more of K to the first sparse pass and keeps a smaller refinement pass could beat the K=24 anchor by using the strongest existing backbone but changing the stage budget structurally for the small-K regime.","summary":"Severe stagnation is now at 16 non-improving rounds, so this round should not do another scalar tweak or reuse another recently losing built-in family. The best next move is a fundamentally different architecture edit on the strongest current backbone: add an asymmetric two-stage soft-codebook variant under `sparsify/` and test it directly at the frontier-relevant K=24 slot with the fixed EF=12/signum/LR=3.2e-3/AUXK recipe.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This keeps one hypothesis and changes architecture only. It is bolder than another built-in retry but still disciplined because it starts from the current winning family rather than inventing a disconnected mechanism. Main risk: asymmetry may simply reduce second-stage correction capacity and underperform the symmetric split, but that is precisely the structural question worth testing under severe stagnation.","needs_sanity":true,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Round 115 should satisfy severe-stagnation policy by introducing a genuinely new architecture instead of another param-only retry after the catastrophic `whitened_lowrank_residual` miss.","Implement `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` as a variant of the existing two-stage soft-codebook family with an intentionally uneven stage budget so more of K is spent in stage 1 and less in stage 2.","Complete the full registration chain before training: add the exact architecture string to `valid_archs`, dispatch it in `_get_sae_class()`, implement the concrete class in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`, then run the exact instantiate/forward/backward smoke test at `(architecture=lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=24, EF=12)`.","Keep the launch contract minimal and exact so the result is attributable to architecture alone at K=24."],"next_hypotheses":["If `lowrank_asymmetric_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` is competitive at K=24, follow with K=16 to test whether asymmetric budget allocation helps even more under tighter sparsity.","If it clearly loses at K=24, continue severe-stagnation search with another structurally different new family rather than returning to selector, routing, or whitening tweaks.","If the exact smoke test passes but the full run fails, summarize the new blocker precisely and repair that architecture-specific issue before judging the family scientifically."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0117_repair_1.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"At smaller K, a single global residual dictionary may be the remaining bottleneck even on the strong soft-codebook backbone. A new `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` family could beat the K=16 frontier by routing samples into different residual dictionaries after the low-rank trunk and soft codebook coarse path, improving conditional specialization without changing the fixed recipe.","summary":"Repaired the original experiment by completing the full integration loop for `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` inside `sparsify/` only. The exact architecture string is now whitelisted in config, dispatched in `_get_sae_class()`, and implemented as a concrete class that keeps the two-stage soft-codebook backbone while replacing each sparse stage scorer with the working norm-bucketed mixture pattern. The required smoke test passed at `architecture=bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=16, EF=12` with forward and backward succeeding on CUDA.","change_type":"edit_sae_code","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual","family_stage":"prototype","self_review":"This repair fixed the actual registration blocker without redesigning the experiment or changing its launch contract. The new family now satisfies the integration checklist: config whitelist updated, factory dispatch added, class implementation present, and the exact target passed instantiate/forward/backward smoke validation.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"16"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":["sparsify/config.py","sparsify/sparse_coder.py"],"notes_to_memory":["Repair round 117 attempt 1 fixed a registration-chain blocker for `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` by adding the exact architecture string to `valid_archs`, wiring `_get_sae_class()` dispatch, and implementing the concrete class in `sparsify/sparse_coder.py`.","The new class keeps the low-rank trunk and soft-codebook coarse path from `lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` and replaces each sparse stage scorer with a norm-bucketed low/high encoder mixture patterned after the working `bucketed_lowrank_residual` family.","Exact smoke test passed for `architecture=bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual, K=16, EF=12` with forward/backward succeeding on CUDA, so the next real run should no longer fail at parse/dispatch time."],"next_hypotheses":["If `bucketed_lowrank_two_stage_soft_codebook_residual` trains cleanly and is competitive at K=16, follow with K=24 to see whether the conditional specialization benefit persists across the mid-K band.","If the full training run now fails with a different runtime or autograd issue, repair that new architecture-specific blocker while keeping the same family and env overrides.","If it trains successfully but clearly loses at K=16, continue severe-stagnation search with another genuinely different new family rather than more soft-codebook conditional variants."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
