research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0021.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625` worsened the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` `K=32, EF=12, LR=3.2e-3` anchor in round 18, reverting only `AUXK_ALPHA` to `0.0` should recover or improve the current frontier-quality point and clarify whether the local aux optimum is actually zero rather than small-positive.","summary":"The last executed run was `lowrank_two_stage_residual` at `K=32, EF=12, LR=3.2e-3, AUXK_ALPHA=0.0625`, so the clean single-variable follow-up is an aux rollback. This avoids another isolation reject and directly tests whether the anchor should use `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` instead of the degraded larger aux setting.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"active","self_review":"This is the safest policy-compliant move because only `AUXK_ALPHA` changes relative to the latest executed recipe. It does not expand the search space, but it resolves the current local ambiguity around the anchor recipe and can still improve the Pareto frontier's best-quality end.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"32"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Rounds 19 and 20 were policy-rejected due to isolation issues; return to a strictly single-variable follow-up from the last executed recipe.","Round 21 rolls back only `AUXK_ALPHA` from `0.0625` to `0.0` at the `lowrank_two_stage_residual` `K=32, EF=12, LR=3.2e-3` anchor to resolve the local aux optimum cleanly."],"next_hypotheses":["If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` beats the current `K=32` frontier point, treat zero-aux as the anchor recipe and then transfer that recipe to a smaller-K slot with a pure `K` change.","If `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0` is still worse than the frontier point, the local optimum likely remains near a small positive aux and a confirming rerun of `AUXK_ALPHA=0.01` becomes justified.","Once the aux setting is settled, prioritize a single-variable `K` reduction from the same recipe to search for a new non-dominated smaller-K point."],"primary_variable":"auxk_alpha"}
