research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0004.json:20:    "summary": "Continue the same-family low-K sweep with a parameter-only run at `K=8`, while pinning the existing low-K recipe (`ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). The `K=16` result was good enough to justify tracing the tail lower before switching families or introducing routing changes.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0004.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0004.json:81:    "description": "Continue the same-family low-K sweep with a parameter-only run at `K=8`, while pinning the existing low-K recipe (`ARCHITECTURE=lowrank_two_stage_residual`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=1.6e-3`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.0`). The `K=16` result was good enough to justify tracing the tail lower before switching families or introducing routing changes.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/logs/agent_action_0162.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"After plain low-rank, two-stage, and grouped residual variants all failed at `K=24, EF=16`, the next severe-stagnation move should still be a fundamentally different existing architecture rather than another minor recipe tweak. `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is the strongest remaining candidate for this slot because routing changes capacity allocation more materially than the recently failed global residual families, and this family historically performed best in the mid-K band even though it has not been given a clean modern `K=24, EF=16` mainline comparison.","summary":"Run an architecture-only comparison at `K=24, EF=16` by switching to `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` while keeping optimizer, LR, aux loss, and preprocessing fixed at the current signum baseline. This follows the severe-stagnation policy to stop minor tweaks, tests a materially different existing family with real mid-K prior signal, and targets a valuable smaller-K slot where a non-dominated point would still improve the frontier.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"full","expected_win":"pareto_tradeoff","family_name":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This is a clean one-variable architecture probe and more policy-consistent than returning to optimizer or preprocessing after repeated misses. The main risk is possible routing fragility, but that is preferable to continuing small recipe tweaks when the search still has untried structurally different existing families with credible mid-K priors.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual"},{"key":"K","value":"24"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"16"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"signum"},{"key":"LR","value":"3.2e-3"},{"key":"AUXK_ALPHA","value":"0.0"},{"key":"USE_HADAMARD","value":"0"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 162 continues severe-stagnation architecture search after grouped low-rank residual coding also failed to improve the `K=24, EF=16` lane.","Hypothesis: `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is the next most informative fundamentally different existing family because routing may help the current mid-K slot more than the recently exhausted plain/grouped residual variants under the fixed modern signum recipe."],"next_hypotheses":["If `routed_lowrank_two_stage_residual` is competitive at `K=24`, follow with `K=16` on the same family to test whether routing extends the frontier further downward.","If it is close but still behind the bucketed backbone, test another fundamentally different existing family at `K=24` rather than returning to scalar recipe tweaks.","If it clearly loses or exhibits routing-specific instability, deprioritize routed residual selection in the current EF=16 regime and continue severe-stagnation search with the next distinct architecture."],"primary_variable":"architecture"}
