research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0060.json:28:    "summary": "Added a new prototype family, `lowrank_multi_branch_residual`, in `sparsify/` and registered it in config/factory dispatch. The architecture applies the existing low-rank trunk first, then mixes three residual encoder branches with a learned sample-level routing head before sparse selection. Exact smoke test passed for `architecture=lowrank_multi_branch_residual, K=24, EF=12`, and a quick encode comparison confirmed behavior differs from `lowrank_residual`. This is a fundamentally different conditional-dictionary architecture for severe-stagnation recovery, not a scalar or K sweep.",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0060.json:37:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0060.json:93:    "description": "Repaired `lowrank_multi_branch_residual` so the original round-60 experiment can run under DDP. The crash was caused by inherited `encoder.weight` and `encoder.bias` from `LowRankResidualSparseCoder` being unused in the new family, which triggered the prior-iteration reduction error. Patched `_mixed_acts()` so the inherited residual encoder is an always-on anchor branch alongside the routed branches, then re-ran the concrete factory-dispatch checks. Validation passed: all parameters now receive gradients, and the exact smoke target `architecture=lowrank_multi_branch_residual, K=24, EF=12` instantiates, runs forward, and backward successfully.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0066.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/14_20260326_184609/logs/agent_action_0006.json:1:{"command":"run","hypothesis":"Adam appears to be the better optimizer for topk at K=128 EF=12, and the 8e-4 callback landed very close to the 1e-3 anchor. A smaller follow-up LR reduction to 9e-4 can answer whether the adam optimum lies between those two settings rather than at either endpoint.","summary":"Keep the topk mainline fixed at K=128 EF=12 with adam and run one more narrow LR refinement at 9e-4 to bracket the best adam operating point.","change_type":"param_only","experiment_tier":"proxy","expected_win":"lower_fvu","family_name":"topk","family_stage":"mainline","self_review":"This keeps the family, K, EF, and optimizer fixed and asks one remaining LR question before moving on to other axes. The 8e-4 result was close enough to the 1e-3 anchor that an in-between LR is the most interpretable next probe.","needs_sanity":false,"env_overrides":[{"key":"ARCHITECTURE","value":"topk"},{"key":"K","value":"128"},{"key":"EXPANSION_FACTOR","value":"12"},{"key":"OPTIMIZER","value":"adam"},{"key":"LR","value":"9e-4"}],"touched_files":[],"notes_to_memory":["Round 6 narrows the adam LR search between 8e-4 and 1e-3 for the current topk K=128 EF=12 mainline."],"next_hypotheses":["If 9e-4 does not clearly beat the existing adam anchor, stop LR tuning and move to a single loss/preprocess-related parameter next.","If 9e-4 improves again, keep adam as mainline and only then consider whether another very small LR refinement is still justified."],"primary_variable":"lr"}
