research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0039.json:20:    "summary": "Continue on the same `gated` mainline and probe only the learning-rate axis. Keep `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, and `OPTIMIZER=signum` fixed, explicitly pin the reference aux/runtime knobs, and raise `LR` from `1.6e-3` to `2.0e-3`. Read the whole curve, not just terminal FVU: if the higher LR preserves stability while improving mid-to-late descent below the refreshed `0.149936` control, then the current anchor was slightly conservative; if it becomes noisier or finishes worse, keep `1.6e-3` as the gated LR anchor and stop the LR branch.",
