research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0054.json:19:    "hypothesis": "Round 53 answered only the upward side of the re-opened LR question on the Hadamard-strengthened `gated` anchor: `LR=2.4e-3` stayed healthy but finished slightly worse than the current `0.142923` best, so the remaining single question is whether the new preprocess actually wants a smaller step size instead of a larger one. With `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1` fixed, does lowering `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` improve the full curve, or does `2.0e-3` remain the best shared mainline setting even after preprocess changed conditioning?",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0054.json:20:    "summary": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0054.json:29:        "key": "ARCHITECTURE",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0054.json:104:    "description": "Stay on the active `gated` mainline and keep the family reference recipe fixed at `ARCHITECTURE=gated`, `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `AUXK_ALPHA=0.03125`, and `USE_HADAMARD=1`. Change only `LR` from `2.0e-3` to `1.6e-3` to complete the downward side of the LR localization around the current Hadamard anchor. Judge this run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if the lower LR yields a smoother mid/late descent and finishes below `0.142923`, then Hadamard shifted the preferred step size downward; if it is flatter or worse, lock `2.0e-3` as the operative mainline LR and stop the LR branch again.",
research/history_archive/16_20260328_220351/round_summaries/round_0076.json:20:    "summary": "Use the one allowed matched architecture probe on `jumprelu`. Keep the current mainline recipe fixed at `K=128`, `EXPANSION_FACTOR=12`, `OPTIMIZER=signum`, `LR=2.0e-3`, and the same aux/runtime settings, and change only `ARCHITECTURE` from `two_stage_residual` to `jumprelu`. Judge the run by the whole trajectory, not just the endpoint: if `jumprelu` stays reasonably close with a healthy curve, keep it in reserve because its thresholded single-stage support path may lower LUTurbo online selection cost; if it is clearly worse throughout, close the probe and return to the `two_stage_residual` mainline next round.",
