research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0156.json:25:    "self_review": "This is a clean single-variable architecture probe using an existing registered family. The main risk is that plain gating may repeat its weak `K=32` result, but `K=24` remains an uncovered tradeoff point and this family is still structurally distinct enough to justify one direct test there before concluding that learned gating is noncompetitive across the current EF=16 small-K lane. It is a more policy-consistent next action than returning to optimizer or preprocessing tweaks after both already failed recently.",
