research/history_archive/13_20260326_175854/round_summaries/round_0062.json:20:    "summary": "Added a new prototype family, `lowrank_soft_codebook_residual`, in `sparsify/` and registered it in config/factory dispatch. The architecture applies the existing low-rank trunk first, then projects the residual through a soft codebook mixture before the usual sparse residual correction. Validation passed on the concrete dispatched architecture: exact smoke test succeeded for `architecture=lowrank_soft_codebook_residual, K=24, EF=12`, and a gradient check showed all parameters receive gradients, so this round stays architecture-only without repeating the prior DDP integration issue.",
